---
import TopicLayout from '../../components/TopicLayout.astro';

const exampleQuestions = [
  'What are the most promising agentic AI frameworks in 2026?',
  'How should I think about deploying AI agents in my organization?',
  'What is the difference between tool use and agentic workflows?',
  'Which companies are leading in AI agent development?',
];

const relatedTopics = [
  { title: 'Context Engineering', href: '/topics/context-engineering' },
  { title: 'Enterprise AI', href: '/topics/enterprise-ai' },
  { title: 'Vibe Coding', href: '/topics/vibe-coding' },
  { title: 'AI Strategy', href: '/topics/ai-strategy' },
];
---

<TopicLayout
  title="AI Agents"
  metaTitle="AI Agents & Agentic Workflows — AmbitiousOS"
  metaDescription="Understanding AI agents, agentic workflows, and autonomous systems. Curated research and analysis from the Reading Ambitiously archive."
  headline="AI Agents & Agentic Workflows"
  intro="AI agents represent a fundamental shift from chatbots to autonomous systems that can plan, reason, and execute multi-step tasks. The agentic revolution is redefining how software is built and how organizations operate."
  exampleQuestions={exampleQuestions}
  relatedTopics={relatedTopics}
>
  <p>
    From tool-calling LLMs to fully autonomous workflows, the landscape is evolving rapidly. Early leaders
    are discovering that the key isn't building smarter models — it's building better scaffolding around
    existing models. Agents that can read, write, search, and execute code are already transforming software
    development, customer support, and data analysis.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Reading Ambitiously archive tracks this evolution across every weekly edition, covering frameworks like
    LangChain, CrewAI, and Claude's tool use, as well as real-world deployments at companies like
    Salesforce, ServiceNow, and Klarna. AmbitiousOS lets you explore this entire body of research through
    AI chat and the interactive knowledge graph.
  </p>
</TopicLayout>
